(version 1)
;; ===========================================================================================
;; pi-runner READ-SCOPE sandbox -- macOS Seatbelt (sandbox-exec) -- PROTOTYPE.
;;
;; Two hard rules for editing this file:
;;   1. Comments are PURE ASCII. The SBPL/TinyScheme reader miscounts multibyte UTF-8 (em-dashes,
;;      ellipses) and then parses comment text as code (an "unbound variable" error).
;;   2. NEVER write a driver placeholder token in a comment. The driver string-substitutes those
;;      tokens; a multi-line scope value spilled into a comment becomes live code and breaks parsing.
;;      Each token below appears ONCE, only at its rule site.
;;
;; WHY: a non-Claude model ignores a prompt-level READING LAW and spelunks files outside its lane (it
;; grepped the whole repo for a phantom component and read 3 OTHER lessons source, bloating context
;; to 116k tokens, then stalled). Prompt rules are unenforceable on weak models, so the scope boundary
;; must live in the OS. Seatbelt is kernel-enforced, INHERITS to every child process (so a spawned
;; grep/find/cat is bound too) and cannot be lifted from inside the sandbox.
;;
;; POLICY: allow everything EXCEPT file reads; deny ALL file reads; then re-allow exactly (1) the
;; toolchain/system roots node+pi+npm need to run and (2) the per-node DECLARED scope the driver
;; injects below. A read of the wider tree (another lesson, or a grep from the filesystem root)
;; returns Operation-not-permitted, while the node own inputs + catalog-digest + shared primitives +
;; node_modules read fine.
;;
;; SCOPE OF THIS PROTOTYPE: it scopes READS only (the incident was a read-scope failure). exec and
;; network are left open (allow default) so the toolchain is unaffected; tighten those later if wanted.
;;
;; The driver (run.mjs buildSandboxProfile) substitutes the home, tmpdir, and declared-scope tokens
;; and writes a per-node copy to the run _pi dir before running sandbox-exec -f <copy> pi <args>.
;; ===========================================================================================

(allow default)

;; Deny every file read up front, then immediately re-allow METADATA everywhere (last match wins).
;; Metadata = stat/traverse, which the toolchain needs to resolve paths (node getcwd / dyld); denying
;; it EPERMs uv_cwd and node never boots. DATA (content) stays denied globally and is re-granted only
;; for the scoped subpaths below -- and content is exactly what the incident leaked: cat/grep read file
;; data, ls/find readdir reads directory data, so both stay blocked for out-of-scope paths.
(deny file-read*)
(allow file-read-metadata)

;; --- toolchain / system roots: node, pi, npm, the dyld shared cache, temp ---
(allow file-read*
  (subpath "/usr")
  (subpath "/bin")
  (subpath "/sbin")
  (subpath "/System")
  (subpath "/Library")
  (subpath "/opt")
  (subpath "/private/var")
  (subpath "/private/tmp")
  (subpath "/private/etc")
  (subpath "/dev")
  (subpath "@TMPDIR@")
  (subpath "@HOME@/.pi")
  (subpath "@HOME@/.npm")
  (subpath "@HOME@/.cache")
  (subpath "@HOME@/.config")
  (subpath "@HOME@/.nvm")
  (literal "/")
  (literal "/etc")
  (literal "/tmp")
  (literal "/var"))

;; --- per-node DECLARED read scope (driver-injected from the node DRIVER-READ-SCOPE marker) ---
;; own lesson inputs + own out dir + the catalog-digest + shared src roots + node_modules. Anything
;; not listed here (other lessons under src/lessons and lesson-data, other out dirs) stays denied.
(allow file-read*
@SCOPE_ALLOWS@)
